artwork: ""
date-released: "2026-05-05"
doi: "10.5281/zenodo.20043593"
url: "https://github.com/mladenpop-oss/bit-pop"
abstract: |
  We present Bit-Pop, a proof-of-concept genomic tool for simultaneous multi-genome
  DNA read classification. The pipeline combines an FM-index based on radix-sort
  suffix arrays for efficient k-mer lookup across all indexed genomes, a bit-level
  2-bit XOR alignment achieving approximately 2.3 ns per 31-base XOR chunk operation, and
  Smith-Waterman local alignment refinement with Phred-scaled quality-aware scoring.
  Benchmarked on simulated Illumina-like reads across three distantly related genomes
  (Escherichia coli, Staphylococcus aureus, and Saccharomyces cerevisiae), Bit-Pop
  achieves 99.9% classification accuracy on correctly mapped reads.
